\section{Conclusion \label{sec16}} In this paper we have introduced SDFEM type nonconforming 
VEM framework for convection dominated convection-diffusion reaction equation. To prove 
polynomial consistency we have assumed higher regularity of approximate 
solution, i.e, $v_{h}|_{T} \in H^{2}(T)$ where $v_{h} \in V^{k}_{h}$. The presented 
framework is not convergent in linear nonconforming virtual element space, i.e. it 
requires piecewise higher order polynomial function$(k\geq 2)$ and $f|_{T} \in H^{s}(T)$ 
where $s \geq 1$ and $T$ is an arbitrary element, which may be considered as light 
drawback of this framework. 

























